Title: Topologizations of Chiral Representations
Authors: Florian Conrady (Heidelberg U. & Potsdam, Max Planck Inst.), Christoph
  Schweigert (Paris U., VI-VII & Aachen, Tech. Hochschul.)
Comments: 23pp
Report-no: HD-THEP-02-10, AEI-2002-085, PAR-LPTHE/02-44, PITHA 02/13
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Mathematical Physics; Functional
  Analysis
\\
  Recently, two different families of topologies have been proposed for
representation spaces of chiral algebras. We prove a theorem that compares the
two types of topologies and show that in one of them chiral blocks are
continuous functionals.
